(b) Calcule la reflectancia DOS y COST de las bandas VIS, NIR y SWIR.

  • Para calcular las reflectancias se aplican los modelos

    $$\rho_{DOS\lambda}=\frac{\pi ( L_{\lambda} - L_{\lambda} )d^2}{ ESUN_{ \lambda } -cos(\theta _{ 0 })}$$

$$\rho_{COS\lambda}=\frac{\pi (L_{\lambda} - L_{\lambda} )d^2}{ ESUN_{ \lambda } -cos^2(\theta _{ 0 })}$$

  • Para calcular las Reflectancias se deben encontrar los valores de ganancia (G) y sesgo (B) para convertir ND de cada banda en radiancia espectral. Se toman los valores de radiancia espectral calculados en el punto anterior.

In [35]:
Esun <- sapply(resp, function(x){
  ## Resample band response to solar spectrum
  resamp  <- approx(x = x[,1], y = x[,2], xout = solar_irradiance[,1])[["y"]]
  ## Convert to relative weights  
  weights <- resamp / sum(resamp, na.rm = TRUE)
  ## Calculated weighted sum
  sum(solar_irradiance[,2] * weights, na.rm = TRUE)            
})

Calculando reflectancia dos para cada banda

In [39]:
# Calculating DOS correction
ac_dos <- image
for(band in bands) {
  fun <- function(x) { (pi * d^ 2 * (x - Lpath[band])) / (Esun[band] * angle) }
  ac_dos[[band]] <- calc(lsx[[band]], fun)
}

#Calculating NDVI

#Toa reflectance
toa_reflectance <- l$band

toa_reflectance$red <- calc( l$band$red, fun=function(x){ 
  angle <- cos( (90 - as.numeric(l$metadata$sun_elevation)) * pi /180 );
  ml <- as.double(l$metadata$reflectance_mult_band_4);
  al <- as.double(l$metadata$reflectance_add_band_4);
  return (x * ml + al) / (angle)
})
toa_reflectance$red

toa_reflectance$nir <- calc( l$band$nir, fun=function(x){ 
  angle <- cos( (90 - as.numeric(l$metadata$sun_elevation)) * pi /180 );
  ml <- as.double(l$metadata$reflectance_mult_band_4);
  al <- as.double(l$metadata$reflectance_add_band_4);
  return (x * ml + al) / (angle);
})
toa_reflectance$nir

ndvi <- (toa_reflectance$nir - toa_reflectance$red) / (toa_reflectance$nir + toa_reflectance$red)

Con base en la funci√≥n condicional definida por el autor se calculan los valores de emisividad de superficie terrestre

In [83]:
#Calculating Land Surface Emissivity

e_v = 0.973
e_s = 0.996
e_w = 0.991
C = 0.005



elambdafunc<- function(x) { 
ndvi_i <- as.numeric(x);
pv <- (( (ndvi_i - ndvi_s) / (ndvi_v - ndvi_s) )^2);
ret <- ifelse(ndvi_i <= 0, 
         e_w,
         ifelse(ndvi_i > 0 & ndvi_i < ndvi_s ,
           e_s, 
         ifelse( ndvi_i >= ndvi_s & ndvi_i <= ndvi_v,
          (e_v * pv + e_s * (1 - pv) + C),
          ifelse(ndvi_i > ndvi_v,
          e_v,
          1
         )
       )));
  return( ret );
}
e_lambda <- calc( ndvi, fun=elambdafunc)
e_lambda

Se calcula la temperatura de la superficie terrestre.

In [84]:
#Calculating LST
boltzmann <- 1.38e-23
planck <- 6.626e-34
lambda <- 1.0895e-5
velocity_of_light <- 2.998e8

p <- planck * (velocity_of_light/boltzmann)

Ts <- BT / (1 + ( (lambda * BT/p) * log(e_lambda) ) )
Ts <- Ts -  273.15
Ts
options(repr.plot.width=5, repr.plot.height=5)
colors <- viridis(50,option = "A")
plot(Ts,main = "Land Surface Temperature (Celsius degrees)",  axes = FALSE, box = FALSE, col=colors)
